monkey boys are the best drink ever. its literally a pitcher filled with like 7 different types of alcohol. A PITCHER OF ALCOHOL!!!! but it gets better because they flavor it so you cant even taste any!  so last night me dan heather justin ryan and my english teacher from last semister (susan martin for any of you i told about her).  we met heather and some other g man people there. we left to go to chumleys for a few hours because its quiet and inexpensive.  then it was back to the saloon to meet everyone else who was there. what a night, drank WAY too much yet again. being 21 is still cool by the way.

P.S. the monkey boys are 5$ during happy hour, and if you can drink more than 3 and walk out of the saloon, i respect you.  they come in a variety of flavors, the best is bong water.

i just had the most intense halluconeginic experience of my life. i apologiz3e for the spelling and typing mistakes, but at this point im surprised i can still function in the realm of concieved reality. for five glorious hours i became PART of the machine, it was all real.


it was all real

im all moved into my new place, and is it ever awesome. im on the 8th floor of beaver terrace (apt 809).  i live right downtown, 2 blocks from where i work, i have a totally AWESOME view from my balcony.  my living room is huge and i have digital cable.  my future room mate michel (for the house in august) is teaching me how to play guitar, so i have my little work area with my bass my guitar and keyboard.  fyi im learning on a hot pink fender stratocaster. HOT PINK!!!!! the bedroom is also too fucking large to be true, there are bunk beds and a regular bed, and i have a walk in closet! and even a table to play poker on (sundays) or eat at.  also i got digital cable so thats even more fun.  i can easily have 20 people inside here with room to move for everybody.  its WAY TOO BIG for 1 person to live in tho.  the best part is accross the hall is dalton's apartment, and next door to me is rachel and andrew, so i have the best neighbors.  well im going to go learn  a little more on my guitar before work. come down and visit people!

oh and 5 days till im 21. yum.

so tomorrow i go to the phil department to apply to be let in. im not nervous cause its not gonna be hard or anything, but im a weird kind of excited. ive been thinking alot about school lately, im really excited to get this started.  i might even go as far as a 12 credit summer semimster, but i doubt that.  ill def be doing at least 18 during normal semisters now however. i need all the extra credits i can get, switching my fucking major this late in my school carrear. i already have a topic for my disortation for grad school, that i didnt even apply to yet.  its great to know what you want to do, but its sublime when you are excited about it.

i fucking love the summer in state college, (for those of you who didnt hear im not coming back).  Ive been out partying with all the cool people who stayed for the last couple days till sunrise.  the friday "chase the semister away" / "goodbye you fucking dorm kids" / "bye friends who arent staying" kegger, and its just been going since there.  it was a sad weekend, had to say goodbye to some friends, but we had a wonderful time.

work is SO fucking boring however, there is nobody in the town so i spend alot of my time being bored.  Im going to be taking a summer class or 2 tho, so that will kill some time.  ive decided in recent days that im not cut out for the journalism major anymore.  the current degrading state of today's media is sickening, and i cant see myself doing work in that feild anymore.  id like to make money AND be able to sleep at night.  now im going to change my major to philosophy.  i know, stop snickering i know its funny,  but ive decided id like to teach college level philosophy for a living.  there is a lack of phil professors at the moment anyway, so the feild has openings.  job opprotunites are a plus, and since you are sort of in demand its even better.  but the interaction with the students in a college level phil class is going to make it worth it.  i get to spend the rest of my life arguing my ideals and thoughts wo a group of students, and getting to hear each of their unique responses, and learn about their viewpoints.  the prospect of waking up to that every day is amazing.  its guarenteed constant mental stimulation every single work day.  every day would be like having a coffee house style conversation with complete strangers all day long, it would never get old or never be the same.

for the first time since i was a freshman im excited about school.  i actually am feeling a passion for what im about to be doing.  im taking some summer classes just so i can get started even sooner. i feel like ive been given a new life, and i cant wait to start it.

you know, i had a good night, i just got the new Nails cd, and i went to grab a glass to get water, well the glass broke in my hand (it was mad cracked) and i just cut the fuck out of my thumb. fuck lol.

Wow, last night was the most fun i have had in a long time.  After taking my english final, i worked at the G-man for like 3 hours. i was SUPPOSED to be quitting, but since i officially live here now, i kind of have to keep working.

went over to the 101 after i was off, and all of us (and there were alot of us) headed over to catharsis, the local "goth" club for some dancing.  There were only about 40 people there, which i guess is kind of standard, but i ran into some friends, danced to some goth music for the first time in FOREVER and smoked a hookah.  Catharsis is in the basement of the Tall Shiva Hookah Lounge, where you can buy a packed hookah (full of tobbacco of course) and chill and smoke with you friends.  It was alot of fun.  

Around 1am we decided to crash the party of some girl that the 101 hates, so off we went. this had to be the LAMEST party ive ever been to, it was an apartment party, but it was like REALLY lame, all there was to drink was queer beer, like smirnof, mikes hard lemonade, and fucking sky blue.  to combat against the lack of alcohol i spilled about 5 cups of fruit punch on the carpet. that should teach the bitch.  this girl apparently stole from the 101 back in the day, and had to be punished. we took some martini glasses, a snow globe, the dimmer switch to her lights and some magnets.  trust me, we got all that was worth stealing.  the only funny (and really sad) part of the party, was the bouncer.  yeah there was a fucking bouncer in an apartment party.  dan and katie started beating the shit out of each other, and the fucking BOUNCER broke it up. it was wrong.

when that got boring we headed back to the 101, and chilled for a while.  alot of people came over and formed sort of an imprompteau after hours party.  i left around 630.  on the way home i passed the water fountain outside of the Biolife building, and somebody put detergent in it, filling it with bubbles.  i called dan and matt and they came and played in the bubbles with me at 7 in the morning, in the middle of a buisy intersection of state college.  what a day.

more to come later, apparently there is a jell-o wrestling party tonite, gotta get ready

so i guess ive been having a good time over sprimng break so far, im not really doing anythign tho. oh and also, just found out today that if i dont give my parents 1000 dollars by the start of next semister, im not going back to school, so that was pretty rockin news to find out. they really want me to get an intership at a newspaper over the summer or something, and it seems all they want me to do is work full time, like 70 hours a week.  i kind of wanted to have fun this summer, VNV Nation, Tiger Army, Nine Inch Nails, Warped, The Cruxshadwos and a bunch of other bands i like will be playing, so i didnt want to miss that.

Now that i think about it tho, i am going to be 21, maybe it is time that a settle down and take on a little responsibility like an internship or something. it would probably be really fun, but i just dont want to be working all summer, i did that once with the holiday inn and it really sucked.  im so not sure what i want to do. part of me wants to be a grown-up but part of me wants to stay a kid and have fun.

this doesnt seem like a hard choice, but i just dont want to let go. i have always hated the idea of a 9-5 job with a 401K, but maybe its time.

Hi Jeff,

Thanks for your comments.  I suppose the devil can take any innocuous term and turn it around for his evil ends.  And to be frank, when the title was created, it was done to indicate that these were promoting groups that were little known, and thus you'd have to see them at out of the way places to check them out.  There was no knowledge of such a street term.

We cannot let groups with an anti-moral agenda keep taking these innocuous terms and changing them around for their own nefarious ends.  They can keep doing this, until there is no more vocabulary we can use to speak!  We have to fight back.  Therefore, if you were to hear the term "back door" again, I invite you to not think of the common street term, but of great Christian musicians that are not yet well-known. 

Thanks again for your letter.

Nick
